-Stud-Gov.png?fit=1000%2C1400&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"1000,1400\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Coup Stud Gov\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/Coup-Stud-Gov.png?fit=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/Coup-Stud-Gov.png?fit=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-874\" style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\" src=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/Coup-Stud-Gov.png?resize=266%2C372&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"266\" height=\"372\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/Coup-Stud-Gov.png?w=1000&amp;ssl=1 1000w, https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/Coup-Stud-Gov.png?resize=214%2C300&amp;ssl=1 214w, https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/Coup-Stud-Gov.png?resize=768%2C1075&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/Coup-Stud-Gov.png?resize=731%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 731w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 266px) 100vw, 266px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The final card on the list, Coup Stud Gov needed another rework since it just gets bounced to the player with the most friends at the start of each year. That made the old Coup Stud Gov only good Senior year, while it is now generally always good. I&#8217;m constantly surprised by how relevant the Stud Gov Pres bonus tends to be.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>What did you think of these balance changes? Let me know in the comments below! Thanks for reading, and make sure to subscribe if you enjoy this content.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Hey everyone! I&#8217;m in the final phases of tweaking in terms of the influence cards. They have overall been pretty balanced, and people have enjoyed them a lot. However, there were a couple of cards that were consistently passed over, indicating that they were not very desirable, or too confusing. One major change is the &#8230; <a title=\"More Influence Card Changes\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/09\/more-influence-card-changes\/\" aria-label=\"More on More Influence Card Changes\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":872,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"spay_email":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/All-Nighter.png?fit=1000%2C1400&ssl=1","jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":895,"url":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/09\/play-testing\/","url_meta":{"origin":868,"position":0},"title":"Mega Post! Photos, Balance Changes, and New Rulebook","date":"September 14, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Hey everyone! I've missed a few posts so I wanted to make it up with a mega-post. I've been doing a bunch of play tests recently, and here are a couple photos: The game is in a good place, and I think that it is pretty balanced. With that in\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Daggers High&quot;","img":{"alt_text":"","src":"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_20180908_173329.jpg?fit=1200%2C900&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200","width":350,"height":200},"classes":[]},{"id":611,"url":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/adjusting-cards-part-four\/","url_meta":{"origin":868,"position":1},"title":"Adjusting Cards (part four)","date":"July 29, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Hey everyone! This time we will be looking at the Junior deck. There were a lot of changes that I made as I found a few persistent issues with the old deck. Because of this, I only explained a few of the changes that I made, and listed the rest\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Daggers High&quot;","img":{"alt_text":"","src":"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Steal-Textbooks-1.png?fit=857%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200","width":350,"height":200},"classes":[]},{"id":527,"url":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/adjusting-cards-part-one\/","url_meta":{"origin":868,"position":2},"title":"Adjusting Cards (part one)","date":"July 20, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Hey everyone! I thought that I would make a series of posts on cards had to be adjusted after play testing, mostly due to balancing issues. The purpose is to showcase more of the process that goes behind the game design of Dagers High. Today, I want to look at\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Daggers High&quot;","img":{"alt_text":"","src":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/playtesthotsauce1.jpg?fit=1033%2C777&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200","width":350,"height":200},"classes":[]},{"id":776,"url":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/08\/sophomore-deck-changes\/","url_meta":{"origin":868,"position":3},"title":"Sophomore deck changes","date":"August 21, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Hey everyone! Today we will be discussing a few of the changes with the Sophomore deck. Sophomore year was designed to be reflective of sophomore year at my school: more difficult classes and less support. Even though the Sophomore deck has a lot more total action points than the Freshman\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Daggers High&quot;","img":{"alt_text":"","src":"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Offensive-Social-Media-Post.png?fit=857%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200","width":350,"height":200},"classes":[]},{"id":592,"url":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/07\/adjusting-cards-part-two\/","url_meta":{"origin":868,"position":4},"title":"Adjusting Cards (part two)","date":"July 27, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Hello everyone! Today I thought I would write a bit about the adjustments I have made recently to the Sophomore deck. These mainly consist of small action point buffs to make Sophomore year a lot less difficult. There is some history to a very difficult Sophomore year: at my high\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Daggers High&quot;","img":{"alt_text":"","src":"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/Final-Exams-1.png?fit=857%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200","width":350,"height":200},"classes":[]},{"id":1007,"url":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/2018\/11\/thanksgiving-update-character-balancing-and-new-essay-changes\/","url_meta":{"origin":868,"position":5},"title":"Thanksgiving update- Character balancing and new Essay changes","date":"November 22, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Happy Thanksgiving everyone! Recently I have been doing a few 2 player play tests with each of the characters to see how strong they are relative to each-other. While I initially planned to do a match up between each possible pair of characters, I quickly found that the new Essay\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Daggers High&quot;","img":{"alt_text":"","src":"https:\/\/i1.wp.com\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/11\/Well-Rounded-1.png?fit=857%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200","width":350,"height":200},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/868"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/jorgezhang.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies